- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper presents a method for mesh generation, which is a common topic in computational geometry.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper proposes a two-phase model with an adaptive control system to improve the mesh quality, which involves numerical methods and analysis.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is another possible category as the paper presents a software implementation of the proposed method.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with generating meshes for graphics applications.
- cs.SI (Systems and Control) is also a less likely category, but the adaptive control system proposed in the paper could be considered as a control system for the mesh generation process.
